8] Remarkably a novelty. Garry the great has played b4 at this point. I guess
one reason for prefering b4 over c4 is to protect a5, thereby freeing Ra1 for
action on the K-side. c4 on the other hand gives added support to d5 - which
can be useful later on if Black tries to free himself with f7-f5 at some point.
